As an active contributor on Answers, it would be nice to have the ability (possibly karma-dependent) to "recommend" a particular question to Atlassian staff.

It is known that staff do not monitor all questions, but sometimes there are questions that can't really be answered by anybody else. In one recent case, I redirected the asker to Bitbucket support, but they categorized the question as "development-related", and told them to take it back to Answers (according to policy). However, the question went unanswered for days because staff didn't happen to notice it. In the meantime, they helpfully answered other questions that didn't require their attention.

I imagine this issue would be more useful for Confluence Questions customers, who may often have staff that spend no time monitoring the site except to moderate spam.

